===Noun===
{{en-noun|~}}
# The [[pelt]] or [[hide]] of a [[yak]]; [[leather]] made from yak hides.
#* '''1933''', {{w|James Hilton (novelist)|James Hilton}}, ''{{w|Lost Horizon}}'', New York: Pocket Books, 1939, Chapter Three, p. 59,<sup>[https://archive.org/details/isbn_0671664271]</sup>
#*: {{...}} there was greater ease in avoiding a scene since wine and fruit were now on offer, having been unpacked by the marching party, stocky Tibetans in sheepskins, fur hats, and '''yakskin''' boots.
#* '''1996''', {{w|Simon Winchester}}, ''{{w|The River at the Center of the World}}'', New York: Picador, Chapter 14, p. 379,<sup>[https://archive.org/details/riveratcentero00simo]</sup>
#*: Down on the banks men were offering ferry rides to the far side in [[coracle]]s made of '''yakskin'''.
#* '''2010''', {{w|David Abrams}}, ''Becoming Animal: An Earthly Cosmology'', New York: Vintage, 2011, pp. 202-203,<sup>[https://books.google.ca/books?id=ryKyB7MATwUC&printsec=frontcover#v=onepage&q&f=false]</sup>
#*: We accepted the invitation to stay at the home of the shaman’s parents, sleeping under '''yak skins''' on the second floor with the rest of the family {{...}}
